Version: 0.1.4
Date: 2026-04-12

Changes:
- Added bilingual README (EN + 中文) with recommended quick start:
  npm install -g merlion
- Improved bash tool reliability:
  autocorrect accidental ".git ..." command prefix to "git ..."
- Wave1 parity hardening:
  bundled ripgrep integration and search/glob/grep behavior alignment
- File tool compatibility alignment:
  read/write/edit support file_path aliases; read supports offset/limit;
  edit supports replace_all
- Artifact hygiene:
  moved generated codebase index from docs/codebase_index.md to
  .merlion/codebase_index.md to avoid polluting tracked docs
- Cache/token observability v2 in CLI:
  added per-turn prompt diagnostics (estimated input tokens, role breakdown,
  role delta, stable-prefix tokens/ratio/hash, provider cache ratio for turn)
  and persisted these metrics into usage jsonl as prompt_observability
  (follow-up fix: tracker now persists across REPL turns and includes tool
  schema tokens in prompt estimate)

Policy:
- For every version change in package.json, add:
  docs/change_log/v<version>.log
